{
  "title": "Garden Maintenance and Tree Planting",
  "transcript": "Hello and welcome to our class on garden maintenance. Tree planting is something many people think about doing, but not everyone knows how to plant one. Today we will be looking at how to do that. The first thing you need to decide is, what exactly do you want to achieve? Do you want your home to look more impressive, or do you want to encourage wildlife to come to your garden? If you know exactly what you want, it will be easier to decide what kind of tree to plant. You'll also need to take into account the weather in the local area before you plant any tree. If you want to attract wildlife, you'll need to make sure your garden can support their habitats. You also need to make sure the soil is appropriate for the kind of trees you want to grow. You can do some online research or go to a local garden center for advice. It's important to make sure you plant your trees at the right time of the year. Then go to the garden center and check out the kind of trees they have on offer, and ask the staff when the best time to plant them is. This will help ensure whether your tree has the best chance of flourishing. Before you do anything, make sure you know how deep the hole should be. Obviously, it should be large enough to accommodate the tree's root ball. Once you've planted the tree, you'll need to water it regularly and keep up a regular schedule of watering so the roots can be established in the surrounding soil. The last thing you need to do is to stand back and appreciate its shade and beauty. You can congratulate yourself on a job well done and on your contribution to the natural environment.[cite: 2]",
